 TOP comedian, actor, musician and entrepreneur, Koffi Nuel Idowu popularly known as ‘Kofi Tha Guru’ has revealed how a show was canceled to avoid the spread of coronavirus. The comedian, in five short videos, said he was engaged for a show but it had to be canceled to avoid the spread of coronavirus. In turn, the entertainer kicked off a private initiative to sensitise his teeming fans and the general public on what they should know about the coronavirus. 